Cook the rice according to package directions. Set aside and keep warm. Place cauliflower in a saucepan; cover with water. Bring to a boil; cook for 5 minutes. Drain and set aside. In a large skillet, saute onion, carrot and garlic in oil until tender. Stir in the ginger, curry, salt and cloves if desired. Add the beans, tomatoes, peas and cauliflower. Cook and stir for 5 minutes or until heated through. Remove from the heat. Serve over the rice.